data.text:
Are you not tired yet? There′s not a whole lot going on in my head We walked around an old museum You told me stories I waited for inspiration to hit Can we go back to when all you had was A picture of me and my first name? Can we go back to when you were impressed By everything that I said? Counting seconds the silence finds I got the hint when you said "nevermind" It's hard to find the common between us Except for this city and our loneliness Can we go back to when all you had was A picture of me and my first name? Can we go back to when you were impressed By everything that I said? Somewhere deep down we′re taken back To a memory we've both had To a time and place less overwhelmed With somebody who makes us feel like ourselves Can we go back to when all you had was A picture of me and my first name? Can we go back to when you were impressed By everything that I said? Writer(s): Elaine Muhlberg, Andrew Tereick
